<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870102-0130 </DOCNO><HL> Offer for Crest-Foam's Shares</HL><DD> 01/02/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CFO LEGTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> MOONACHIE, N.J.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Crest-Foam Corp. said 1.2 million of its common shares have been acquired under the previously announced tender offer by Landamp;P Foam.    Landamp;P is a partnership consisting of units of Leggett andamp; Platt Inc. and Pacific Dunlop Ltd.    As previously reported, the terms call for Crest-Foam holders to receive $14.50 a share. The maker of polyurethane foam said that about 7% of its shares remain outstanding; these will be converted into the right to receive $14.50 each.    Carthage, Mo.-based Leggett makes springs for furniture and bedding. Pacific Dunlop, a manufacturing concern, is based in Melbourne, Australia. </TEXT></DOC>